panied by detailed annotations clarify the text, identifying people, events and concepts, an introduction, and bibliography.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aMedieval History. 4aMilitary History. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Western.2bisacsh  a12th century.  aChronicle.  aCount Baldwin V.  aCount Philip of Flanders.  aEmperor Frederick Barbarossa.  aEmpire.  aEuropean history.  aFrance.  aGilbert of Mons.  aHainaut.  aKing Philip Augustus.  acampaigns.  achurches.  acrusades.  acustomary practices.  agenealogical.  alay advocates.  alord-tenant relationships.  amilitary matters.  anoble marriages.  anoble women.  apolitical events.  asaints.  asieges.  atournaments.1 aNapran, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781846153815?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846153815423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846153815/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles